<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100308564196158></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100308564196158><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=zones.html?zstrat=62&mid=100308564196158>SOLOING!!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=zones.html?zstrat=62&mid=100308564196158#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=40799><span id=Scholar>Xiarro</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Oct 14th 2:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok everyone...heres the deal.<br>I see people asking if they can solo here.  The fact is.. It is really hard to do because of all of the adds in the house.  I have seen a lot of people soloing the whole house.  But they are usually 45 or higher and most of the time they are NOT warriors.  Necros can run around everywhere just saying, PET ATTACK and they can win, unless they get too many.  So i guess what it comes down to is that yes you can solo here at level 20.  Will you die trying?  probably.  So just know where u can and cant solo by trying it.  Dont let others say no cause anything is possible with luck and experience.<br>&nbsp;<br>Xiarrogoningo</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
